item.description:
Write a file using echo # Simply specifying a file destination, echo will create, write, or append to a file.
&lt;echo file=example.txt&quot; append=&quot;false&quot;&gt; hello world &lt;/echo&gt; Print the contents of a file # To print the contents of a file, we can use loadfile to read a file into a local property, and then use echo to print the value of it.
&lt;loadfile property=&quot;contents&quot; srcFile=&quot;example.txt&quot; /&gt; &lt;echo message=&quot;${contents}&quot; /&gt;
